AN African National Congress (ANC) member of the National Assembly was arrested on Friday, 20 January, in Klerksdorp, North West. The member has been under the portfolio committee of Minerals Resources and Energy since 2019. The 34-year-old was arrested for the alleged murder of his 31-year-old wife. National cops spokeswoman Brigadier Athlenda Mathe confirmed the case against the suspect. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments The incident happened on 27 November 2022 at the home of the suspect in Kanana outside Klerksdorp. “The suspect faces a charge of murder, and will appear before the Orkney Magistrates Court on Monday, 23 January,” said Mathe.